review_text: Walk this place almost daily, year 'round. I tend to avoid in the summer as it is full of people and they litter the place it is unbelievable. Early morning or late at night is a great time for walking your doggy and there is no one and you can unlawfully unleash it and have it have a few good runs or  play with other members of its speecie. Makes happy tired dogs, they appreciate.
The park is wonderful for short and long walks, cross-country skiing and other activities around the year.
Beautiful and safe park to walk through

(Translated by Google) Very pleasant park, many cyclists, but not too noisy and crowded. Linhe, when the weather is good, the blue sky and green land, with the surrounding buildings and animals and plants, is quite peaceful and peaceful, very suitable for one person to distract, but also suitable for three or five friends to shake. The only fly in the ointment is that there are a lot of mosquitoes, otherwise it will be perfect. But is nature still natural if there are no mosquitoes?

(Original)
很愜意的公園，很多自行車騎士，卻又不過度喧鬧擁擠。臨河，天氣好的時候藍天綠地，搭配周圍的建築與動植物，相當寧靜祥和，非常適合一個人來散心，也適合三五好友來晃晃。唯一美中不足的地方是蚊蟲有點多，不然就完美了。不過大自然沒有蚊蟲的話還是大自然嗎？

(Translated by Google) I love going for a walk in Parc Desmarchais! For the marina and the path on the edge of the water! For the park, the bike path, the water games and the creamery! And lately, for QUAI 5160; the magnificent house of Verdun culture! It's an appointment with nature and culture!

(Original)
J'adore aller me promener au Parc Desmarchais! Pour la marina et le sentier sur le bord de l'eau! Pour le parc, la piste cyclable, les jeux d'eau et la crèmerie! Et dernièrement, pour le QUAI 5160; la magnifique maison de la culture de Verdun! C'est un rendez-vous avec la nature et la culture!
